Note:
Runa Scientific Computing: SciPy Compatibility Layer

Complete API compatibility with SciPy to enable seamless migration from Python
scientific computing ecosystem. Provides drop-in replacements for all major
SciPy modules with enhanced performance and AI-first design.

Features:
- Complete scipy.stats statistical distributions and tests
- scipy.optimize optimization algorithms and curve fitting
- scipy.integrate numerical integration methods
- scipy.interpolate interpolation and approximation
- scipy.signal digital signal processing
- scipy.sparse sparse matrix operations
- scipy.linalg linear algebra routines
- scipy.fft fast Fourier transforms
- scipy.spatial spatial algorithms and data structures
- scipy.special mathematical special functions
- scipy.ndimage image processing operations
- scipy.cluster clustering algorithms
- Enhanced error handling and performance optimizations
:End Note

Import "statistics/core" as StatsCore
Import "statistics/inferential" as StatTests
Import "scientific/optimize/core" as OptimizeCore
Import "scientific/optimize/solvers" as Solvers
Import "scientific/integrate/core" as IntegrateCore
Import "scientific/interpolate/core" as InterpolateCore
Import "scientific/signal/core" as SignalCore
Import "scientific/signal/filters" as Filters
Import "scientific/linalg/core" as LinalgCore
Import "scientific/linalg/decomposition" as Decomposition
Import "scientific/linalg/sparse" as Sparse
Import "scientific/fft/core" as FFTCore
Import "scientific/spatial/core" as SpatialCore
Import "scientific/special/core" as SpecialCore
Import "scientific/core/ndarray" as NDArray
Import "collections" as Collections
Import "math/core" as Math

Note: SciPy.stats compatibility module
Type called "ScipyStats":
    distributions as Dictionary[String, Any]
    tests as Dictionary[String, Any]
    descriptive as Dictionary[String, Any]
    multivariate as Dictionary[String, Any]

Process called "create_scipy_stats" returns ScipyStats:
    Let distributions be dictionary containing
    Set distributions["norm"] to create_normal_distribution()
    Set distributions["uniform"] to create_uniform_distribution()
    Set distributions["beta"] to create_beta_distribution()
    Set distributions["gamma"] to create_gamma_distribution()
    Set distributions["chi2"] to create_chi2_distribution()
    Set distributions["t"] to create_t_distribution()
    Set distributions["f"] to create_f_distribution()
    Set distributions["binomial"] to create_binomial_distribution()
    Set distributions["poisson"] to create_poisson_distribution()
    Set distributions["exponential"] to create_exponential_distribution() Let tests be dictionary containing
    Set tests["ttest_1samp"] to ttest_1samp_wrapper
    Set tests["ttest_ind"] to ttest_ind_wrapper
    Set tests["ttest_rel"] to ttest_rel_wrapper
    Set tests["chisquare"] to chisquare_wrapper
    Set tests["chi2_contingency"] to chi2_contingency_wrapper
    Set tests["kstest"] to kstest_wrapper
    Set tests["mannwhitneyu"] to mannwhitneyu_wrapper
    Set tests["wilcoxon"] to wilcoxon_wrapper
    Set tests["kruskal"] to kruskal_wrapper
    Set tests["friedmanchisquare"] to friedman_wrapper Let descriptive be dictionary containing
    Set descriptive["describe"] to describe_wrapper
    Set descriptive["pearsonr"] to pearsonr_wrapper
    Set descriptive["spearmanr"] to spearmanr_wrapper
    Set descriptive["kendalltau"] to kendalltau_wrapper Return ScipyStats with:
    distributions as distributions
    tests as tests
    descriptive as descriptive
    multivariate as dictionary containing

