Note: Statistical test wrappers
Process called "ttest_1samp_wrapper" that takes args as List[Any] returns Any:
    Let data be args at index 0
    Let popmean be args at index 1
    Return StatTests.one_sample_ttest with sample as data and population_mean as popmean

Process called "ttest_ind_wrapper" that takes args as List[Any] returns Any:
    Let sample1 be args at index 0
    Let sample2 be args at index 1
    Let equal_var be if Collections.List.length with lst as args is greater than 2 then args at index 2 else true
    Return StatTests.two_sample_ttest with sample1 as sample1 and sample2 as sample2 and equal_variances as equal_var

Process called "ttest_rel_wrapper" that takes args as List[Any] returns Any:
    Let sample1 be args at index 0
    Let sample2 be args at index 1
    Return StatTests.paired_ttest with sample1 as sample1 and sample2 as sample2

Process called "chisquare_wrapper" that takes args as List[Any] returns Any:
    Let observed be args at index 0
    Let expected be if Collections.List.length with lst as args is greater than 1 then args at index 1 else None
    Return StatTests.chi_square_goodness_of_fit with observed as observed and expected as expected

Process called "chi2_contingency_wrapper" that takes args as List[Any] returns Any:
    Let observed be args at index 0
    Return StatTests.chi_square_independence with contingency_table as observed

Process called "kstest_wrapper" that takes args as List[Any] returns Any:
    Let sample be args at index 0
    Let distribution be args at index 1
    Return StatTests.kolmogorov_smirnov_test with sample as sample and distribution as distribution

Process called "mannwhitneyu_wrapper" that takes args as List[Any] returns Any:
    Let sample1 be args at index 0
    Let sample2 be args at index 1
    Return StatTests.mann_whitney_u_test with sample1 as sample1 and sample2 as sample2

Process called "wilcoxon_wrapper" that takes args as List[Any] returns Any:
    Let sample1 be args at index 0
    Let sample2 be if Collections.List.length with lst as args is greater than 1 then args at index 1 else None
    Return StatTests.wilcoxon_signed_rank_test with sample1 as sample1 and sample2 as sample2

Process called "kruskal_wrapper" that takes args as List[Any] returns Any:
    Return StatTests.kruskal_wallis_test with samples as args

Process called "friedman_wrapper" that takes args as List[Any] returns Any:
    Return StatTests.friedman_test with samples as args

Note: Descriptive statistics wrappers Process called "describe_wrapper" that takes args as List[Any] returns Any:
    Let data be args at index 0
