    Return StatsCore.spearman_correlation with x as x and y as y

Process called "kendalltau_wrapper" that takes args as List[Any] returns Any:
    Let x be args at index 0
    Let y be args at index 1
    Return StatsCore.kendall_tau_correlation with x as x and y as y

Note: Optimization wrappers
Process called "minimize_wrapper" that takes args as List[Any] returns Any:
    Let fun be args at index 0
    Let x0 be args at index 1
    Let method be if Collections.List.length with lst as args is greater than 2 then args at index 2 else "BFGS"
    Return OptimizeCore.minimize with objective as fun and initial as x0 and method as method

Process called "minimize_scalar_wrapper" that takes args as List[Any] returns Any:
    Let fun be args at index 0
    Let method be if Collections.List.length with lst as args is greater than 1 then args at index 1 else "brent"
    Return OptimizeCore.minimize_scalar with objective as fun and method as method

Process called "root_wrapper" that takes args as List[Any] returns Any:
    Let fun be args at index 0
    Let x0 be args at index 1
    Let method be if Collections.List.length with lst as args is greater than 2 then args at index 2 else "hybr"
    Return Solvers.find_root with equations as fun and initial as x0 and method as method

Process called "curve_fit_wrapper" that takes args as List[Any] returns Any:
    Let f be args at index 0
    Let xdata be args at index 1
    Let ydata be args at index 2
    Let p0 be if Collections.List.length with lst as args is greater than 3 then args at index 3 else None
    Return OptimizeCore.curve_fit with model as f and x_data as xdata and y_data as ydata and initial_params as p0

Process called "least_squares_wrapper" that takes args as List[Any] returns Any:
    Let fun be args at index 0
    Let x0 be args at index 1
    Return Solvers.least_squares with residuals as fun and initial as x0

Process called "differential_evolution_wrapper" that takes args as List[Any] returns Any:
    Let fun be args at index 0
    Let bounds be args at index 1
    Return OptimizeCore.differential_evolution with objective as fun and bounds as bounds

Process called "basinhopping_wrapper" that takes args as List[Any] returns Any:
    Let fun be args at index 0
    Let x0 be args at index 1
    Return OptimizeCore.basin_hopping with objective as fun and initial as x0

Note: Integration wrappers
Process called "quad_wrapper" that takes args as List[Any] returns Any:
    Let func be args at index 0
    Let a be args at index 1
    Let b be args at index 2
    Return IntegrateCore.adaptive_quadrature with func as func and lower as a and upper as b

Process called "dblquad_wrapper" that takes args as List[Any] returns Any:
    Let func be args at index 0
    Let a be args at index 1
    Let b be args at index 2
    Let gfun be args at index 3
    Let hfun be args at index 4
    Return IntegrateCore.double_integral with func as func and x_lower as a and x_upper as b and y_lower as gfun and y_upper as hfun

Process called "tplquad_wrapper" that takes args as List[Any] returns Any:
    Let func be args at index 0
    Return IntegrateCore.triple_integral with func as func

Process called "fixed_quad_wrapper" that takes args as List[Any] returns Any:
    Let func be args at index 0
    Let a be args at index 1
    Let b be args at index 2
    Let n be if Collections.List.length with lst as args is greater than 3 then args at index 3 else 5
    Return IntegrateCore.gauss_legendre_quadrature with func as func and lower as a and upper as b and points as n

Process called "quadrature_wrapper" that takes args as List[Any] returns Any:
    Let func be args at index 0
    Let a be args at index 1
    Let b be args at index 2
    Return IntegrateCore.gaussian_quadrature with func as func and lower as a and upper as b

Process called "romberg_wrapper" that takes args as List[Any] returns Any:
    Let func be args at index 0
    Let a be args at index 1
    Let b be args at index 2
    Return IntegrateCore.romberg_integration with func as func and lower as a and upper as b

Process called "trapz_wrapper" that takes args as List[Any] returns Any:
    Let y be args at index 0
    Let x be if Collections.List.length with lst as args is greater than 1 then args at index 1 else None
    Return IntegrateCore.trapezoidal_rule with y_values as y and x_values as x

Process called "simps_wrapper" that takes args as List[Any] returns Any:
    Let y be args at index 0
    Let x be if Collections.List.length with lst as args is greater than 1 then args at index 1 else None
