Process called "romb_wrapper" that takes args as List[Any] returns Any:
    Let y be args at index 0
    Let dx be if Collections.List.length with lst as args is greater than 1 then args at index 1 else 1.0
    Return IntegrateCore.romberg_rule with y_values as y and spacing as dx

Process called "solve_ivp_wrapper" that takes args as List[Any] returns Any:
    Let fun be args at index 0
    Let t_span be args at index 1
    Let y0 be args at index 2
    Return IntegrateCore.solve_initial_value_problem with derivatives as fun and time_span as t_span and initial_values as y0

Process called "odeint_wrapper" that takes args as List[Any] returns Any:
    Let func be args at index 0
    Let y0 be args at index 1
    Let t be args at index 2
